article_title: Jets’ Season Comes Down to Stopping the Unstoppable Gronkowski
article_text:
The last time the Jets tried to stop Rob Gronkowski, they failed. In a Week 7 matchup two months ago, the New England Patriots’ All-Pro tight end racked up 11 catches for 108 yards and the game-sealing touchdown in a 30-23 win, sending the Jets into a slide in which they lost four of five games.

If the Jets are serious about making the playoffs, which will almost certainly require a win over New England on Sunday in East Rutherford,...
